Business Brief -- Saint Louis S.A.:
   Stake of 53.89% in Concern
   Is Held by Two Companies
The SBF noted that it decided on Dec. 4 to exempt Worms
and Saint Louis from launching a takeover bid for the entire
company, reasoning that Worms, with nearly 50% itself,
already had effective control over the company.
   A breakdown of the two companies' stakes revealed that
Worms controls 49.454%, while IFIL has 4.45%.
   Officials at Saint Louis, Worms and IFIL weren't available
for comment.